channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Best supermarket for Xmas dinner savings
item.description: Christmas dinner staples could cost Australian families 45 per cent more depending on where they choose to stock up on essentials, experts have warned.

item.title: Bus driver charged over deadly Bondi crash
item.description: A bus driver has been charged over a crash in Sydney’s Bondi suburb that left at 24-year-old woman dead.

item.title: Crown’s gaming licence under threat
item.description: Melbourne’s Crown Casino is under threat of losing its licence with the Victorian government bringing forward an investigation into the controversial gaming venue.

item.title: This type of sunscreen could be deadly
item.description: Relying on aerosol sunscreens could be deadly this summer, with a host of dodgy products deemed ineffective by alarming new research, skin cancer experts have warned.

item.title: $4.4bn windfall scrapped amid China spat
item.description: Record Chinese demand for iron ore driving up prices for Australian exporters will barely register in conservative new budget figures, with the government opting not to factor in a $4.4 billion potential windfall amid the pandemic and rocky relations with China.

item.title: Urgent virus warning for numerous venues
item.description: Health authorities are pleading with anyone who visited a number of sites on Sydney’s Northern Beaches to get tested and isolate immediately after two new cases were reported on Wednesday afternoon.

item.title: Kids flee crash in alleged stolen car
item.description: Dashcam footage has captured the moment a group of children allegedly crashed two stolen cars before fleeing in another stolen vehicle north of Brisbane.

item.title: Huge change to SA borders
item.description: SA Police will stand down from border checkpoints effective immediately, the commissioner has declared, without consulting the state’s top public health officer.

item.title: ‘No let up’: Huge storm warning
item.description: A huge portion of New South Wales is bracing for heavy rain and flash flooding as a storm surges across the state with warnings in place on Wednesday evening for more than a dozen cities including Sydney.

item.title: Victim arrested after WA bikie shooting
item.description: The man who was shot by a suspected sniper alongside slain Rebels boss Nick Martin in Perth is back behind bars after allegedly breaching the terms of his parole by associating with bikies.
